<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-11T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-11T08:00:00-05:00" n="880" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d880">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/938</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-11T14:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">January 11, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>My telegram No. 451, January 8. Finnish commission had audience
                                yesterday with the King of Norway, who welcomed Finland as <pb facs="0832" n="742" xml:id="pg_742"/> an independent sister
                                nation of Scandinavia. One of the members of the commission named
                                    <persName corresp="#p_RJN1">Reuter</persName> will shortly leave
                                for England and the United States.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>